LOCAL FIX: Store the next pointer in a temporary variable before deleting the current node.
--- a/program.cpp
+++ b/program.cpp
@@ -10,7 +10,8 @@
     /* Walk from the head to the tail, deleting each node as we go.
      * Called when the owning container is destroyed. */
-    for (Node *cur = head; cur != nullptr; cur = cur->next) {
+    for (Node *cur = head; cur != nullptr; ) {
+        Node *next = cur->next;
         delete cur;
+        cur = next;
     }
 }

GLOBAL FIX: Use smart pointers (std::unique_ptr) to manage the lifetime of the nodes automatically, which eliminates the need for manual memory management and prevents this class of use-after-free bugs entirely."
"}

